STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
Victor THIGPEN, Appellant. No. ED 106602 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION ONE. Filed: May 21, 2019 FOR APPELLANT: Kristina Starke Olson, Anna Callan Moench, Public Defender Office, 1010 Market Street, Suite 1100, St. Louis, MO 63101. FOR RESPONDENT: Eric S. Schmitt, Attorney General, Julia E. Rives, Asst. Atty. Gen., P.O. Box 899, Jefferson City, MO 65102. Before Roy L. Richter, P.J., Sherri B. Sullivan, J., and Robert M. Clayton III, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Victor Thigpen appeals the judgment entered on a jury verdict convicting him of five counts of first-degree statutory sodomy and one count of first-degree statutory rape. We find no error has occurred.

No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have, however, provided the parties a memorandum setting forth the reasons for our decision. The judgment of the trial court is affirmed under Rule 30.25(b).
